@page "/profiles"

<PageTitle>Profiles — DrunkDeer</PageTitle>

@* A page rather than a dashboard tab (FUTURE_PLAN §5.3): a profile covers the whole board, so
   unlike the actuation and lighting panels it has nothing to do with the key selection, and
   nothing to gain from sitting beside the keyboard. *@

<MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mb-4">Profiles</MudText>

<MudGrid>
    <MudItem xs="12" md="7" lg="5">
        <ProfilePanel />
    </MudItem>
    <MudItem xs="12" md="5" lg="7">
        <MudPaper Class="pa-4" Elevation="1">
            <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Class="mb-2">About profiles</MudText>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Secondary" Class="mb-2">
                A profile is the board's actuation depths, lighting, and rapid-trigger setting saved
                together. They're stored in this browser, and export to a JSON file the
                <code>deerkb</code> command-line tool reads and writes — the two use the same format.
            </MudText>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Secondary">
                A profile only records what this session actually set. The keyboard can't report its
                own settings back, so anything configured before you connected — or in another app —
                isn't visible here and won't be saved.
            </MudText>
        </MudPaper>
    </MudItem>
</MudGrid>
